Press Release<br />Transcript Presscon<br /><!-- NewsDate.start -->April 18, 2006<!-- NewsDate.end --><p style="text-align: center">
<font size="3">Pangilinan: </font>On the Cha Cha<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span></p>
<!-- NewsBody.start --><p style="text-indent: 25px">As was already previously.. 
nabanggit ni Senator Pimentel, a number of senators are preparing to undertake a 
campaign, and education and information campaign on the issue of Charte Change. 
Two resolutions on Charter Change passed by the Senate two weeks ago, before we 
went on recess, there was a consensus among several senators that there was a 
need to do more. May consensus kami na kailangang gumawa pa ng ibang hakbang 
aside from yung pagpapasa ng resolution sa Chacha para mapa-abut ito sa publiko. 
So we have been undertaking a series of consultation meetings dahil gusto natin 
Makita ang pananaw, punto de visto, at mga hakbang na isinasagawa ng ibang mga 
grupo, ibang mga indibidwal hinggil nga dito sa usaping Charter Change. So today 
we met with some individuals representing some groups who are also concerned 
about the manner in which the Charter Change campaign is being undertaken. And 
we hope to be able to go full blast in this effort to educate the public on the 
issue of Charter Change on the basis of our resolutions, we will inform the 
public as well bakit kami nagpasa ng dalawang resolusyon tungkol sa ConAss at 
Peoples Initiative, ano ang dahilan dito, bakit 23 ang pumirma, ang nadlagda sa 
una at 21 naman sa pangalawa, palagay namin ay ito ang mas makakabuti para sa 
publiko na nagkakaroon ng magandang panunuring o maayos na pagsusuri dito sa 
usapin ng Charter Change. So we hope to be able to undertake a more organized, 
systematic education campaign wherein a number of senators will be directly 
participating.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Meron nang ilang mga efforts na, for example I came 
back from General Santos yesterday and I was in Davao also and I undertook my 
own separate individual education awareness campaign on the 2 resolutions. 
Senate resolution 77 and (478) on Con Ass. If youll also notice, perhaps some 
of you have noticed that before the Holy Week break, some senators have been 
vocal about their position on Charter Change, particularly senators Gordon, 
senator Roxas also issued a statement on plans of the senate in terms of 
education and information, senator Pimentel. This is all part of the coordinated 
efforts of the senators in addressing the need to raise awareness ng ating mga 
kababayan dito sa usapin ng pagbabago n gating Saligang Batas.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">In fact maliwanag yan dun sa aming pagpupulong, we 
are not against Chacha per se. and both resolutions are clear. It is not that we 
oppose Charter Change, but we oppose the manner in which they are proposing how 
we are to undertake it. Di naman tayo tutol sa Charter Change, kung Charter 
Change lang ang pinaguusapan. Pero ang sabi nga naming, kung may imumungkahi sa 
pagbabago ng Saligang Batas, dapat irerespeto yung proseso. At hindi dapat labag 
sa Saligang Batas at labag sa ating mga batas yung pagbabago, o yung effort na 
baguhin an gating Saligang Batas.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Again, ang basehan natin ay yung dalawang 
resolution na ipinasa ng senado. Yung unang resolution, dapat voting separately. 
Ang ConAss dapat voting separately. Hindi pwedeng voting as one. So yun an 
gating basehan kung bakit kinakailangan ipaliwanag sa publiko na hindi 
pupuwedeng 195 signatures na sinasabi ng Kongreso at pupuwede nang umpisahan 
yung pagbabago, yung mga process of proposing amendments to the Constitution. So 
yan, sinasabi natin sa publiko kung bakit di pupuwede yan. Pangalawa, dun naman 
sa Peoples Inititative. Sinasabi rin natin sa resolusyon na dahil sa Supreme 
Court ruling, walang enabling law, pangalawa, Inititative can only be to amend 
not to revise and pangatlo, kung DILG ang nagpapatakbo nito eh mukhang resources 
ng gobyerno ang ginagamit, which again is contrary to the spirit of the 
Constitutional provision on Inititative na dapat taong bayan, yung ordinary 
citizens at hindi yung gobyerno o taong gobyerno yung nagtutulak. So we are in 
effect saying that while we agree with Charter Change as a concept per se, I 
mean many of us do, we do not agree in the process being pushed by government, 
by congressmen and by some groups and individuals. Kasi dapat unahin yun eh, 
bago nating pagusapan kung babaguhin ba natin yung Saligang Batas o hindi, kung 
baga, hindi puwedeng lumarga yun tren hanggat hindi, kung walang prankesa. So 
first things first, eto bang effort na to ay legal o illegal? And then and only 
then can we start discussing other areas of Constituional Change such as whether 
Parliamentary is better, etc. that is one of the issues we are raising. And then 
kasama dun sa proseso syempre yung pagmamadali. Sa atin, naniniwala din tayo 
dapat may transparency. Hindi naman pupuwedeng June 15 tapos na ang boksing. 
That is only 60 days from now. Yung proseso din, talaga bang nagkakaroon ba ng 
malalim na pagaaral dito sa mga sinasabing minumungkahi dito sa Peoples 
Initiative? Sabi shift from a Presidential-Bicameral to a Unicameral- 
Parliamentary. Ang tanung dyan eh alam ba ng taung bayan o maliwanag ba sa taung 
bayan na kapag ganun ang nangyari, eh gusto ba nilang hindi na sila ang boboto 
sa ating Presidente? Yun, conveniently hindi nakakasama dito sa diskusyon. So 
dapat we are also concerned about the process in which the Charter Change 
proponents are pushing the Chacha agenda.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Binubuo pa natin [ang mechanics] but, for example, 
yesterday, pinulong ko ang ilang mga local official sa region 12 at pinaliwanag 
ko sa kanila yung dalawang resolusyon ng Senado. Tapos nagkaroon ng mga 
katanungan. So ganun ang isang paraan. It is a dialogue we hope to go to the 
schools also. Ang ating mga kabataan we hope yung mga nagsasummer class, yung 
iba kasi, bakasyon but yung mga summer class, siguro education fora. I have 
received invitations for example mula sa academe, mula sa Ateneo, for me to be a 
speaker sa mga Chacha discussion nila. And this is ibaibang campuses, hindi lang 
dito sa Maynila pati ang ibatibang campuses ng Ateneo, for example, are 
interested to find out more about etong Charter Change.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Of course, apart from the students, we also have 
civic organizations, NGOs, local government officials, my own view is that there 
are a lot of local officials who are not, contrary dun sa sinasabi ng ilang mga 
proponents ng Charter Change na solido ang mga local officials sa pagbabago ng 
Saligang Batas, hindi totoo yun. Contrary rin dun sa sinasabing may clamor daw 
sa buong Pilipinas para sa Charter Change, ang sa General Santos, sa Davao city, 
at sa iba pang part eng ating bansa, hindi nila alam kung saan nanggagaling ang 
clamor for Charter Change na yun. So meron silang mga kampanya na pinapakitang 
mukhang tapos na ang boksing pero ang taung bayan mismo ang nagtataka. Sa 
maraming parte ng Pilipinas, anong ibig sabihin nung bakit sinasabi nilang July, 
bat sinasabi nila June tapos na? so we can see na kapag nabigyan ng tamang 
impormasyon an gating mga kababayan, mas nauunawaan nila itong usapin ng Charter 
Change at lalong nagkakaroon ng agam-agam dito sa mga tinutulak na minamadali 
yung Chacha.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Sa huling banda, ang taung bayan mismo ang 
magsasabi kung sino ang kapanipaniwala at kung sino ang hindi kapanipaniwala. So 
it is really the people in the end who will decide, based on our education and 
information effort hindi naman tayo ang magpapasya nyan, in fact, if youwant to 
be strict about it, ang talagang magpapasya sa Chacha ay yung taong bayan mismo. 
Tayo dyan ay nagbibigay lamang pagkakataon na magpaliwanag dun sa usapin.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Siguro maaga pa sabihin kung matutuloy ang 
plebiscite o hindi. Yun ang gusting mangyari nung pumipilit na mgka-plebiscite 
na. Pero sa atin, ito ay kampanya talaga para malamn talaga ng taung bayan kung 
bakit pumosisyon ang senado na illegal itong Initiative na ito, malaman ng taong 
bayan ano yung desisyon ng Korte Suprema sa Santiago vs Comelec, malaman ng 
taong bayan ang itinutulak na ConAss, kung bakit hindi pupuwedeng voting jointly 
or together. So ito ang gusto nating palalimin pa, paguawa n gating bayan dito 
sa usaping Charter Change.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Dun sa mga paguusap naming dun sa Core Group nung 
Senate effort, hindi lamang education campaign ang magiging hakbang ng pagkilos 
na ito, pinagaaralan din ng mga legal cases na maaring isampa para magkaroon ng 
liwanag dito nsa legal questions na ito. So this is not just an education 
information drive but I think the bulk of it will be the education information 
drive pero tinitingnan din natin, we are also looking at the other action points 
including the possible filing of cases. So this is not, we are not limiting the 
Senates actions to purely education and information. We are not limiting 
ourselves to that.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Pinagusapan din ang funding and we will probably 
have to find ways and means from concerned citizens. It is an official act of 
the Senate, we may allocate some funds for public information dissemination but 
obviously may mga limits yun.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Marami sa mga rank and file ng DILG, rank and file 
ng Comelec, ay may agam agam din eh. Dahil alam nila may Supreme Court ruling na 
hindi pwede gawin ito tapos ginagawa nila. So maaari silang managot. So merong 
dilemma. Nabasa natin yung isang liham ng former chairman ng Comelec na si 
Chairman Monsod, sabi niya meron talagang mga nasa probinsya na Comelec 
employees na may agam agam dito sa pirma na ito, sa initiative na ito. And so 
ito ay panawagan na rin dun sa ating mga kasamahan sa gobyerno, our Comelec 
officials, our Comelec employees, rank and file DILG employees na magisip isip 
sila dahil maari ring meron silang pananagutang administratibo dito sa gawaing 
ito. Kaya siguro may mga hindi umaamin dahil may posibilidad na may pananagutan 
sila dito.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">We are concerned because the act is illegal. We did 
not undertake an illegal act. And I think it is our duty, if an act is illegal, 
that we inform the public. The public has a right to know if the funds are being 
utilized for an illegal purpose. Iba yung sitwasyon. Una, hindi kami ang 
nagsagawa nung Initiative. Yung illegal na Initiative. At tungkulin naming 
bilang senador to act as a check and balance on the executive. And so therefore, 
dapat ipaliwanag sa publiko kung bakit ito illegal kung bakit hindi dapat 
gumagamit ng pondo ng gobyerno para sa isang illegal na gawain. In connection 
with Senate reolution 77 specifically yung expressing the sense of the Senate 
yung illegal itong Initiative. Pero I need to stress that the resources of the 
Senate are limited and we can only spend so much. There are limitations to what 
we can spend for public information and dissemination.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">I think each senator has a budget for public 
information and dissemination, it can come from that already, it does not have 
to be a new budget.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">So far those who have expressed their interest in 
going around the country are 8 or 9 senators. This is both opposition and 
administration, majority and minority. Senator Pimentel, Drilon, Osmena, myself, 
Roxas, Cayetano, Gordon, I believe senator Lacson, senator Biazon and several 
others. But I have not spoken to the others directly so I cannot speak on their 
behalf. But those that I have mentioned, I have spoken to them personally and 
they are all interested in participating in an effort to raise the awareness of 
the public dito sa usapin ng Charter Change.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 25px">Hindi pa nafa-finalize ang timetable but we will 
try to cover as much ground as possible. But its just a matter now of scheduling 
the different senators. During recess and even after. Senator Flavier also is 
also supportive of the effort. That is at least 10. yun ang mga personal na 
nakausap ko. At personal na nagpahiwatig ng kanilang interes na suportahan yung 
education campaign.</p>
